1. Why are functions advantageous to have in your programs?

  functions are an advantage because it helps us avoid coding again and again and it saves time . it also makes the code more undertandable


2. When does the code in a function run: when it's specified or when it's called?

 code runs when a function is called and gets executed from firstnline of the code 
 
 
3. What statement creates a function?
 
 THE keyword def creates a function
 eg) def test():

4. What is the difference between a function and a function call?

 A function is a code  which has a specific operation to perform and
 Function call is when you call a function so it runs the code and gives the output 


5. How many global scopes are there in a Python program? How many local scopes?
 
 only one global scope per program and remains until we terminate it and the scope created inside the funtion is called local scope 

6. What happens to variables in a local scope when the function call returns?
 
 calling a function  creates a new local variable eachtime and therefore it expires after a function call returns 

7. What is the concept of a return value? Is it possible to have a return value in an expression?

A return statement is used to return values from a function, it can be usd outside a funtion
 Yes we can use return value in an expression


8. If a function does not have a return statement, what is the return value of a call to that function?

A function without a return statement will return NONE

